{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.20",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 20,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 20 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:1",
      "text": "Wine is a mocker, strong drink is raging: and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:2",
      "text": "The fear of a king is as the roaring of a lion: whoso provoketh him to anger sinneth against his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:3",
      "text": "It is an honour for a man to cease from strife: but every fool will be meddling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:4",
      "text": "The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold; therefore shall he beg in harvest, and have nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:5",
      "text": "Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water; but a man of understanding will draw it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:6",
      "text": "Most men will proclaim every one his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:7",
      "text": "The just man walketh in his integrity: his children are blessed after him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:8",
      "text": "A king that sitteth in the throne of judgment scattereth away all evil with his eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:9",
      "text": "Who can say, I have made my heart clean, I am pure from my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:10",
      "text": "Divers weights, and divers measures, both of them are alike abomination to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:11",
      "text": "Even a child is known by his doings, whether his work be pure, and whether it be right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:12",
      "text": "The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the Lord hath made even both of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:13",
      "text": "Love not sleep, lest thou come to poverty; open thine eyes, and thou shalt be satisfied with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:14",
      "text": "It is naught, it is naught, saith the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasteth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:15",
      "text": "There is gold, and a multitude of rubies: but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:16",
      "text": "Take his garment that is surety for a stranger: and take a pledge of him for a strange woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:17",
      "text": "Bread of deceit is sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:18",
      "text": "Every purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice make war.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:19",
      "text": "He that goeth about as a talebearer revealeth secrets: therefore meddle not with him that flattereth with his lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:20",
      "text": "Whoso curseth his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in obscure darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:21",
      "text": "An inheritance may be gotten hastily at the beginning; but the end thereof shall not be blessed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:22",
      "text": "Say not thou, I will recompense evil; but wait on the Lord, and he shall save thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:23",
      "text": "Divers weights are an abomination unto the Lord; and a false balance is not good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:24",
      "text": "Man’s goings are of the Lord; how can a man then understand his own way?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:25",
      "text": "It is a snare to the man who devoureth that which is holy, and after vows to make enquiry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:26",
      "text": "A wise king scattereth the wicked, and bringeth the wheel over them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:27",
      "text": "The spirit of man is the candle of the Lord, searching all the inward parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:28",
      "text": "Mercy and truth preserve the king: and his throne is upholden by mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:29",
      "text": "The glory of young men is their strength: and the beauty of old men is the gray head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.20.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 20,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 20:30",
      "text": "The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil: so do stripes the inward parts of the belly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
